CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "Nominating Committee - The newly elected nominating committee, which will choose a slate of candidates for positions on the executive board of the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP is shown above. They are Mrs. Carrie Reid, Mrs. Louise Payne, Mrs. Sophia Nelson, McKinley Tomlin, Malvin Goode, Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr. and Atty. Donald Stocks.  Members of the committee not shown are Mrs. Edythe Perkins, Frank E. Bolden, William Ford and Mrs. Elvira Marks. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Four men and six women, including woman wearing dark shirred hat, gathered at table in Ebenezer Baptist Church during NAACP membership meeting
